2 slice Sourdough Bread
4 ounce Fresh Mozzarella
1 unit Tomato
2 ounce Arugula
3 tablespoon Parmesan Cheese
½ cup Guacamole
1 teaspoon Chili Flakes
5 teaspoon Balsamic Glaze
1 teaspoon Olive Oil
Salt
Pepper

• Toast bread. Wash and dry produce.

• Thinly slice mozzarella into rounds. Thinly slice tomato into rounds;
season with salt and pepper.

• In a large bowl, combine arugula, Parmesan, and a drizzle of olive oil.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.

• Spread guacamole onto toasted bread. Season with salt, pepper, and a
pinch of chili flakes. Top with mozzarella and seasoned tomato.

• Halve toasts on a diagonal; divide toasts and salad between plates.
Drizzle everything with as much balsamic glaze as you like. Serve.